It may lay claim to being the 'Happiest Place on Earth', a magical kingdom ruled by fairytale princesses and the like, but even Disneyland was still built with bricks, mortar and hard graft.

The only theme park to have been completely overseen by Walt Disney himself, Disneyland Park, celebrates 60 years in 2015 and extensive celebrations are planned.

A time-lapse video from the Disney archives reveals how the park, which forms half of the Disneyland Resort in Anaheim, California, was built from nothing before its opening on July 17, 1955.

