From an expanse of brown dirt, iconic features such as Tomorrowland's Rocket to the Moon are raised into place while Sleeping Beauty Castle emerges like a turbo episode of Grand Designs. 

Other original features rising from the earth include the Main Street Train Station's clock tower, the shell for jungle-themed Adventureland and rocky Old West throwback Frontierland. 

Looking down Main Street USA to the original Fantasyland, Sleeping Beauty's Castle forms perhaps the most iconic image of the park, which emerges like a mini-town in Orange County.

Later years have seen the introduction of New Orleans Square in 1966, Critter Country in 1972 and Mickey's Toontown in 1993, followed by an entirely new Disney California Adventure Park in 2001 - together they are now known as Disneyland Resort. 

