Far from the fantasy Walt  would have hoped for it was labelled internally as 'Black Sunday' after a number of operational mishaps that range from chaotic queues to a gas leak in Fantasyland that closed Fantasyland, Frontierland and Adventureland for the afternoon.  

But it was merely a minor setback for what is now Disney's Parks and Resorts division which now overseas Anaheim's Disneyland Resort, Walt Disney World Resort in Floria, Tokyo Disney Resort, Disneyland Paris, Hong Kong Disneyland Resort and Shanghai Disney Resort, a fleet of cruise liners and a host of hotels. 

And just like the end of this timelapse, which show the first guests arriving in Anaheim, millions continue to flood through the turnstiles - more than 130 million a year, in fact.

